{"article_id":"K3vmllEt9YLHyyXh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Anti-Semitic attacks continue to shake our city and state .","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"Last week , eight attacks","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"- including four in just 48 hours -","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"sent a familiar shock wave rippling through the Jewish community .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Then on Saturday came the horrific stabbing in Monsey , New York .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"The poison of Jew-hatred is spreading .","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"Like many of you , I ' m thinking ,","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"\" Not this subject again. \"","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"How many columns can be devoted to it ?","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"I ' ve read them .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"I ' ve written them .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"It ' s exhausting ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"and it ' s dreary .","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"Jews are being beaten up ,","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"anti-Semitism flows some years","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"and ebbs in others .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"So what ?","depth":4},{"id":17,"text":"Mayor Bill de Blasio released his usual by-the-numbers statement .","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"\" Hate doesn ' t have a home in our city , \"","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"But hate does have a home here ,","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"and it has found it","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"while Hizzoner has mostly looked away .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"The mayor added :","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"\" In light of recent anti-Semitic attacks , the NYPD will increase their presence in Borough Park , Crown Heights and Williamsburg. \"","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"But the recent attacks have spread to Midtown Manhattan and Gravesend , Brooklyn .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"The problem has gotten worse","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"while inaction paralyzed the mayor .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"I first wrote about the uptick in May .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"The reason","depth":15},{"id":30,"text":"the city ' s liberal political class was ignoring it ,","depth":15},{"id":31,"text":"I argued ,","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"is that the criminals don ' t fit their picture of Evil Bigots .","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"They aren ' t , for the most part , MAGA hat-wearing white guys with tiki torches .","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"In fact , many of the attackers are people of color ,","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"as investigative reporting by Tablet ' s Armin Rosen and others has shown .","depth":14},{"id":36,"text":"Imagine","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"if they were white nationalists .","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"How much faster would the mayor and other city leaders have taken action ?","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"\" A lot of folks were told","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"it was unacceptable to be anti-Semitic , \"","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"de Blasio said in May .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"\" It was unacceptable to be racist ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"and now they ' re getting more permission. \"","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"The message was subtle but unmistakable :","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"De Blasio was trying to pin the attacks in bright-blue New York on President Trump .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"see also De Blasio 's whitewashing on anti-Semitism","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"Here ' s what ' s been happening in New York City over the ...","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Hizzoner didn ' t surrender the fantasy for some time .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"In June , he said :","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"\" I want to be very , very clear ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"the violent threat , the threat","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"that is ideological ,","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"is very much from the right . \"","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"He left unclear how the Big Apple had come to be populated by ideological far-right types","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"beating up on Jews .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"His comments underscored his inability","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"to truly counter the type of street-level anti-Semitism","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"spreading through the city .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"Will he face the facts now ?","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Or will Jews need to actually die ,","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"not just be pummeled ,","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"for our leaders to grasp the threat ?","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"\" Anti-Semitism is an attack on the values of our city","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"-","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"and we will confront it head-on , \"","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"de Blasio tweeted","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"after this latest round of violence against Jews in the city .","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"He has to stop beating around the bush .","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"These attacks aren ' t an attack on \" our values. \"","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"They ' re attacks on visibly Jewish people .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Even Sunday , after the Monsey stabbings ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"he blamed Trump and \" Washington \" for creating \" an atmosphere of hate . \"","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"De Blasio needs to stop trying to find a \" them \" to be the opposite of his \" us. \"","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"His juvenile obsession","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"with having the right adversaries","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"allows anti-Semitism to flourish .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"I used to write about Europeans and their apathetic attitudes toward the Jew-hatred around them .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"Synagogues torched ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Jews beaten","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"- just another day on the Continent .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"But now the demon is here , in America .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"Worse , it ' s stalking Jews with increasing regularity in New York City , my city , home to the largest Jewish population outside Israel .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Hizzoner ' s vague universalist rhetoric obscures this raw reality .","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"And it isn ' t just his ideological blinders .","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"The mayor has also helped create an anti-police atmosphere ,","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"in which the vigilant presence of officers is considered a bad thing .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"At an anti-police rally last month , there were signs","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"calling for violence against the NYPD .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"De Blasio ' s response ?","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"He insinuated","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"that the idea","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"that there ' s anti-police sentiment in our city","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"is , yes , another right-wing plot .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"In 2020 , I don ' t want to read another column like this one .","depth":4},{"id":95,"text":"All Jews want is to live our lives in safety .","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"To ensure that ,","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"the mayor will have to stop using the violence against us","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"to fight his invisible political foes .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"De Blasio ' s ideology has led to apathy ,","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"which , in turn , has resulted in injured Jews in our city .","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"It ' s time for his administration to take serious action ,","depth":5},{"id":102,"text":"starting by flooding hot-spot neighborhoods with police officers","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"empowered to act .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"In May , I wrote :","depth":5},{"id":105,"text":"\" The attacks , and the silence of progressive New York , are utterly appalling. \"","depth":5},{"id":106,"text":"In December , it ' s more than appalling .","depth":5},{"id":107,"text":"It ' s complicit .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":215,"left":184,"right":214,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent"